1. Modes of Communication:
The main form of communication will be through email. If the message is urgent, a mass text may be sent out in order to notify the group members to check their email. Teammates are expected to respond to an email within 12 hours during the week and within 24 hours during the weekend.
Google chat, text messages, and Facebook shall be used as secondary modes of communication.
Documents to be worked on will be shared through Google Documents. All team members are expected to contribute to a shared document. 
A Google group has been created (in4matx-151-team-j@googlegroups.com) as a way to collectively contact one another.  
A Facebook group has also been created to handle the social gatherings and schedule potential lunches/dinners as a group.  

2. Code of Conduct
Each team member must actively participate in all meetings and in creation of  documents. 
Each team member must do their assigned task to their fullest extent and on time

2.1. Open forum for communication
Members of Team Jamminâ€™ shall be accepting of otherâ€™s opinions and always open to constructive criticism.  Individual members should always speak their minds without fear of antagonism and all members will listen attentively and respectfully.  

2.2. All members must seek help whenever necessary
Team Jamminâ€™ is dedicated to success individually and as one cohesive unit.  As such, all team members must not be afraid to seek help when need be.  The success of the team is completely determined by the success of each individual.  If one of us fails, we all fail.

2.3. All members must input equal effort
Each member must participate equally in all meetings and assignments.  No one person should feel burdened to do a majority of the work.  This is a team project, so each member must participate to their maximum potential for the team to succeed.
	
2.4. All members must hold one another to the highest standard of respect and work ethic
Team Jamminâ€™ has a strict no harassment policy.  We hold the â€œGolden Ruleâ€ in the highest regard and strive earnestly to treat one another as we would like to be treated.  Likewise, we will consistently put in 110% effort if we expect our fellow team members to do the same. 

	2.5. Work Hard, Play Hard
Team Jamminâ€™ is not only dedicated to putting in an effort of 110% on all tasks and work   but shows the same amount of effort when it comes to relaxing and playing. It is important to sharpen the saw before cutting down a forest.

3. Weekly Meetings
Weekly meetings will occur every Tuesday from 6:30 to 7:30 pm (or longer if necessary), during which the team will discuss, plan, and work on various documents/deliverables. The team will meet more frequently as the project becomes more complicated. This time frame can be adjusted (if necessary) with a majority vote from the group (3 out of 5 members).  
The Google Calendar will be used to coordinate schedules if additional meetings are necessary. Team members are expected to update their calendars regularly so they are accurate. 
At the end of every meeting, an e-mail with the recap of topics discussed will be sent out immediately before adjourning.
3.1. Tardiness, Absences, and Incompletion of Assigned Tasks
If a team member is late to a meeting, regardless of the amount of time, the team will take 5-10 minutes to recap on the topics that had been discussed in their absence. 
In the event that a team member is late or absent from a meeting, the meeting will be conducted regardless of their presence. 
If unable to meet set deadlines or scheduled meetings, inform all group members within 48 hours before meeting and one week before the set deadlines for assignments via the modes of communications established in previous section.

3.1.1 Tardiness without Prior Notification
If a team member is more than ten minutes late, that person must supply snacks or drinks for the other members. 
If a team member is more than 30 minutes late, that person must do something of the other members collective choice. 
If a team member is more than 1 hour late, that person must make up the lost productivity by picking up additional work.

3.1.2 Absence or Incompletion of Assigned Task without Prior Notification
If a team member fails to notify the entire team, he/she will be penalized by treating all other team members to dinner (With a maximum of $20).
3.1.3 Tardiness or Absence with Prior Notification
If a team member appropriately notified the group ahead of time, no extreme measures will be taken. 
If that team member excessively continues to be tardy and/or absent, then the that team member will be penalized by treating all other team members with dinner ($20 spending limit).  

4. Amending the Covenant
The terms of this covenant can be added to/changed/amended providing 100% of all members agree to the amendments.
